<subSubSection id="18D9310FFA98B7F2C2180604AB423A10" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="BF1FB659D9CAC8DDC396EB70258044D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CFFFF2AE6664F735FD2996978906D7CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A subspecies endemic to the Balkan Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation id="4766F01D4000C43FC2BCAD2502DA7C40" author="Strid, A." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669378" refString="Strid, A., 1986. Mountain flora of Greece 1. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Mountain flora of Greece 1" year="1986">Strid 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3EE1935F0EB6006F49D007B1778B4B8B" author="Aybeke, M." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 13 (3): 433 - 455" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667824" refString="Aybeke, M., Dane, F., 2007. New floristic records in the Balkans: 6. Phytologia Balcanica, 13 (3): 433-455" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 6" year="2007">Aybeke and Dane 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In the floristic region of NE Greece, there are records from Mt. Pangeo, Mt. Menikio, Mt. Falakro, Mt. Orvilos and Mt. Lekani. The new locality on Mt. Achladovouno forms the easternmost border of its distribution range in Greece.
</paragraph>
